<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="537" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1052,2016]" box="[151,749,1052,1079]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,749,1052,1079]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,749,1052,1079]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1837" box="[151,252,1052,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Haplidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,252,1052,1079]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">Haplidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1855" box="[311,473,1052,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Haplidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissa">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[311,473,1052,1079]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">Haplidia fissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, historical background
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1052,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">
The genus name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1837" box="[347,429,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Aplidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[347,429,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">Aplidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hope, F. W." box="[657,801,1089,1115]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="15 - 121" refId="ref7163" refString="Hope, F. W. (1837) The Coleopterist's Manual, containing the lamellicorn insects of Linneus and Fabricius. Henry G. Bohn, London, xiii + [2] + 15 - 121 + [4] pp., 3 pls." type="book chapter" year="1837">Hope (1837)</bibRefCitation>
to accommodate a single taxon, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1801" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1801" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Melolontha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversa">
<emphasis box="[1180,1436,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">Melolontha transversa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[151,327,1125,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" refId="ref7030" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1801) Systema Eleutheratorum secundum ordines, genera, species: adiectis synonymis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Tomus II. Bibliopoli Academici Novi, Kiliae, 687 pp." type="book" year="1801">Fabricius, 1801</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<typeStatus box="[338,386,1125,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Burmeister, H. C. C." box="[628,834,1124,1151]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" refId="ref6743" refString="Burmeister, H. C. C. (1855) Handbuch der Entomologie. Vierter Band. Besondere Entomologie. Fortsetzung. Zweite Abtheilung. Coleoptera Lamellicornia Phyllophaga chaenochela. Theod. Chr. Friedr. Enslin, Berlin, x + 569 pp." type="book" year="1855">Burmeister (1855)</bibRefCitation>
recognized a second species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1855" box="[1166,1306,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Aplidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissa">
<emphasis box="[1166,1306,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">Aplidia fissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a Syrian—Mesopotamian female specimen whose re-examination was apparently neglected by all following authors. As a matter of fact, various subsequent identifications, descriptions of new species, and compilations of systematics catalogues for the genus seem to have been often based on literature alone, without re-examination of specimens, namely 
<typeStatus box="[243,306,1269,1295]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">types</typeStatus>
. One of such catalogues (
<bibRefCitation author="Harold, E. von" box="[601,746,1269,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="979 - 1346" refId="ref7107" refString="Harold, E. von (1869) [new names]. In: Gemminger, M. &amp; Harold, B. von: Catalogus coleopterorum hucusque descriptorum synonymicus et systematicus. IV. Scarabaeidae. E. H. Gummi, Monachii, pp. 979 - 1346 + [7]." type="journal article" year="1869">Harold 1869</bibRefCitation>
) also introduced the incorrect subsequent spelling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1837" box="[1330,1430,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Haplidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1330,1430,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">Haplidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was retained for over a century (
<emphasis box="[592,632,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">e.g.</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter, E." box="[646,789,1305,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="93 - 303" refId="ref7798" refString="Reitter, E. (1902) Bestimmungs-Tabelle der Melolonthidae aus der europaischen fauna und angrenzenden landern, enthaltend die gruppen der Pachydemini, Sericini und Melolonthini. Verhandlungen des Naturforschenden Vereines in Brunn, 40, 93 - 303. [1901]" type="journal article" year="1902">Reitter 1902</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Grandi, G." box="[801,945,1304,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="159 - 224" refId="ref7069" refString="Grandi, G. (1925) Contribute alla conoscenza biologica e morfologica di alcuni Lamellicorni fillofagi. Bollettino del Laboratorio di Zoologia Generale e Agraria della Facolta Agraria in Portici, 18, 159 - 224." type="journal article" year="1925">Grandi 1925</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrovitz, R." box="[957,1124,1304,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="204 - 206" refId="ref7648" refString="Petrovitz, R. (1958) Eine neue Haplidia - Art aus Kleinasien (Coleopt., Scarabaeidae). Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali e del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale in Milano, 97, 204 - 206." type="journal article" year="1958">Petrovitz 1958</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrovitz, R." box="[1135,1194,1305,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="325 - 343" refId="ref7692" refString="Petrovitz, R. (1967) Ergebnisse zoologischer sammelreisen in der Turkei. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 70, 325 - 343." type="journal article" year="1967">1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrovitz, R." box="[1205,1264,1305,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="38 - 45" refId="ref7719" refString="Petrovitz, R. (1970) Scarabaeidae aus Iran. Entomologie et Phytopathologie Appliquees, 29, 38 - 45." type="journal article" year="1970">1970</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrovitz, R." box="[1276,1346,1305,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="215 - 238" refId="ref7741" refString="Petrovitz, R. (1971 a) Scarabaeidae from the Near East. Israel Journal of Entomology, 6, 215 - 238." type="journal article" year="1971">1971a</bibRefCitation>
, b; 
<bibRefCitation author="Viggiani, G." pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="89 - 152" refId="ref8037" refString="Viggiani, G. (1969) Richerche sulla entomofauna del Nocciulo. 1. Contributo alla conoscenza della Haplidia etrusca Kr. (Col. Scarabaeidae). Note morfoetologiche e mezzi di lotta. Bollettino del Laboratorio di Entomologia Agraria Filippo Silvestri, 27, 89 - 152." type="journal article" year="1969">Viggiani 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Viggiani, G." box="[287,346,1341,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="11 - 15" refId="ref8088" refString="Viggiani, G. (1977) Nuovi reperti su alcuni coleotteri radicicoli (Haplidia etrusca Kr., Otiorrhynchus armatus Boh., O. trophonius Reitt.). Bollettino del Laboratorio di Entomologia Agraria Filippi Silvestri, 34, 11 - 15." type="journal article" year="1977">1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carpaneto, G. M." box="[359,542,1341,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="111 - 126" refId="ref6789" refString="Carpaneto, G. M. (1979) Observazioni sui coleotteri Scarabaeoidea delle Isole Ponziane. Fragmenta Entomologica, 15, 111 - 126." type="journal article" year="1979">Carpaneto 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baraud, J." box="[555,703,1340,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="191 - 196" refId="ref6465" refString="Baraud, J. (1975) Descriptions de cinq nouvelles especes palearctiques de Coleopteres Scarabaeoidea. Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, 5, 191 - 196." type="journal article" year="1975">Baraud 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baraud, J." box="[716,775,1341,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="1 - 352" refId="ref6492" refString="Baraud, J. (1977) Coleopteres Scarabaeoidea. Faune de l'Europe occidentale Belgique-France-Grande-Bretagne-Italie- Peninsule Iberique. Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, 7 (Supplement 4), 1 - 352." type="journal article" year="1977">1977</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baraud, J." box="[787,846,1341,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="539 - 580" refId="ref6524" refString="Baraud, J. (1988) Contribution a l'etude du genre Haplidia Hope (Coleoptera Scarabaeoidea Melolonthidae). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 95, 539 - 580. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 79672" type="journal article" year="1988">1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baraud, J." box="[858,917,1341,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="159 - 162" refId="ref6569" refString="Baraud, J. (1990) Description de deux nouvelles especes du genre Haplidia Hope (Coleoptera, Scarabaeoidea, Melolonthidae). Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, 7, 159 - 162." type="journal article" year="1990">1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baraud, J." box="[930,989,1341,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" refId="ref6603" refString="Baraud, J. (1992) Coleopteres Scarabaeoidea d'Europe. Faune de France 78. Societe Lineenne de Lyon, Lyon, xi + 856 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / linly. 1992.11007" type="book" year="1992">1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sabatinelli, G." box="[1002,1189,1341,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="5 - 50" refId="ref7842" refString="Sabatinelli, G. (1991) Note sul genere Haplidia Burm. con descizione di H. baraudi n. sp. Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 123, 4 5 - 50." type="journal article" year="1991">Sabatinelli 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Coca Abia, M. M. &amp; Martin Piera, F." pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="69 - 77" refId="ref6903" refString="Coca Abia, M. M. &amp; Martin Piera, F. (1993) The genus Haplidia Hope, 1837 (Coleoptera, Melolonthidae) in the Iberian Peninsula. Nouvelle Revue d'Entomologie, 10, 69 - 77." type="journal article" year="1993">Coca Abia &amp; Martìn Piera 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Keith, D." box="[289,431,1377,1403]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="380 - 387" refId="ref7237" refString="Keith, D. (2000 a) Contribution a la connaissance des Scarabaeoidea du Moyen Orient: taxons nouveaux ou peu connus (Coleoptera). Lambillionea, 100, 380 - 387." type="journal article" year="2000">Keith 2000a</bibRefCitation>
, b; 
<bibRefCitation author="Coca Abia, M. M." box="[474,661,1377,1403]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="220 - 227" refId="ref6852" refString="Coca Abia, M. M. (2004) External morphology and genitalia of Melolontha melolontha (L., 1758) (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Melolonthinae). A comparative study with other genera of the Iberian Peninsula. Laimburg Journal, 1, 220 - 227." type="journal article" year="2004">Coca Abia 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesarini, C." box="[673,831,1377,1403]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref7626" refString="Pesarini, C. (2004) Insetti della Fauna Italiana Coleotteri Lamellicorni. Natura, 93, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="2004">Pesarini 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Keith, D. &amp; Lo Cascio, P." box="[844,1129,1376,1403]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="139 - 142" refId="ref7375" refString="Keith, D. &amp; Lo Cascio, P. (2005) A new Haplidia Hope from Nisyros Island (Dodecanese, Greece) with a catalogue of the genus. Lambillionea, 105, 139 - 142." type="journal article" year="2005">Keith &amp; Lo Cascio 2005</bibRefCitation>
). The original spelling was reintroduced by recent authors such as 
<bibRefCitation author="Chikatunov, V. &amp; Pavlicek, T." box="[583,927,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="37 - 65" refId="ref6815" refString="Chikatunov, V. &amp; Pavlicek, T. (1997) Catalogue of the beetles (Coleoptera) in Israel and adjacent areas: 1. Scarabaeoidea. Klapalekiana, 33, 37 - 65." type="journal article" year="1997">Chikatunov &amp; Pavlíček (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana, A. &amp; Kral, D." box="[1078,1342,1413,1440]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="207 - 228" refId="ref7942" refString="Smetana, A. &amp; Kral, D. (2006) Rhizotrogini. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Volume 3. Scarabaeoidea-Scirtoidea-Dascilloidea-Buprestoidea-Byrrhoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 207 - 228." type="book chapter" year="2006">Smetana &amp; Král (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezdek, A." pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="249 - 280" refId="ref6643" refString="Bezdek, A. (2016) Rhizotrogini. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 3. Scarabaeoidea, Scirtoidea, Dascilloidea, Buprestoidea, Byrrhoidea. Revised and updated edition. Brill, Leiden, Boston, pp. 249 - 280." type="book chapter" year="2016">Bezděk (2016)</bibRefCitation>
and in recent contributions (
<emphasis box="[553,594,1450,1475]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">e.g.</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Boyer, J. - C." box="[609,745,1449,1475]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="39 - 40" refId="ref6703" refString="Boyer, J. - C. (2014) Aplidia transversa transversa (F. 1801), nouveau pour la faune de France (Coleoptera Scarabaeidae Melolonthinae Rhizotrogini). L'Entomologiste, 70, 39 - 40." type="journal article" year="2014">Boyer 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Miessen, G." box="[757,918,1449,1475]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="57 - 73" refId="ref7539" refString="Miessen, G. (2016) Essais sur le genre Aplidia Hope 1837 a Chypre et commentaires sur quelques especes limitrophes (Coleoptera, Scarabaeoidea, Melolonthidae, Rhizotrogini). Entomologie Faunistique-Faunistic Entomology, 69, 57 - 73." type="journal article" year="2016">Miessen 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soldati, F. &amp; Noblecourt, T. &amp; Barnouin, T." box="[930,1142,1449,1475]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="371 - 372" refId="ref7993" refString="Soldati, F., Noblecourt, T. &amp; Barnouin, T. (2016) Presence d' Aplidia transversa (F., 1801) dans les Alpes-Maritimes (Coleoptera Scarabaeidae Melolonthinae). L'Entomologiste, 72, 371 - 372." type="journal article" year="2016">
Soldati 
<emphasis box="[1017,1075,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mienis, H. K." box="[1154,1299,1449,1475]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="3 - 4" refId="ref7502" refString="Mienis, H. K. (2017) Activity pattern of the Cockchafer Aplidia chaifensis in Kibbutz Netzer Sereni, Israel, in 2017. Natuurhistorische en Andere Notities, 14, 3 - 4." type="journal article" year="2017">Mienis 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lambert, G. &amp; Lemaire, J. - M." pageId="1" pageNumber="537" pagination="13 - 14" refId="ref7453" refString="Lambert, G. &amp; Lemaire, J. - M. (2018) Confirmation de la presence du hanneton Aplidia transversa (Fabricius, 1801) (Coleoptera Scarabaeidae Melolonthinae) dans les Alpes-Maritimes (France). Biocosme Mesogeen, 35, 13 - 14." type="journal article" year="2018">Lambert &amp; Lemaire 2018</bibRefCitation>
). However, based on Article 33.2.3.1 (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[746,881,1485,1511]" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" refId="ref7211" refString="ICZN, (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
), the spelling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1837" box="[1039,1139,1485,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Haplidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1139,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">Haplidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be retained as correct, as being in prevailing usage and attributed to the original author and date. Consequently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1855" box="[1210,1368,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Haplidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fissa">
<emphasis box="[1210,1368,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="537">Haplidia fissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the original combination for Burmeister’s taxon (Article 33.3.1).
</paragraph>
